Steps to create ruleserver:

1. under <service-module>.jar create a folder  named rulesets
2. under ruleset create a folder specific name of ruleset. example: bplassessment
3. create a file under it called agendagroup
3. create folders under as follows:
	  facts = where facts are located. files end with .drl
	  rules = for system rules. files end with .drl
      schema = subdivided further in actions and facts 
		  facts = files end with .fact 
		  actions = files end with .action
		  
      templates = where templates are located. files end with .gtpl
      	  
directory summary:
   <module>
	  |_ rulesets
		    |_ <rulesetname>
					|_agendagroups*
					|_ facts
						  |_ <fact>.drl*
					|_ rules
						  |_ <rulename>.drl
					|_ schema
						  |_ facts
							    |_ <factdef>.fact
						  |_ actions 		
							    |_ <actiondef>.action
					|_ templates
						   |_ actions
								 |_ <actionname>.gtpl
		  
Example:

.action
{
	name: "Test Action",
	template: "test-action",
	params: [
		{ name: "message", datatype: 'string', caption: 'Message', expression:true },
	]
}

.fact
{
	name: "CurrentDate",
	title: "Current Date",
	package: "com.rameses.util", 
	factclass: "DateBean",
	index:1,
	agendagroup: ".*",
	fields: [
		{name: "day", datatype:"integer", caption:"Day of Month" },
		{name: "year", datatype:"integer", caption:"Year" },
		{name: "month", datatype:"integer", caption:"Month" },
	]
}

